# Technical slide deck rule

Use this rule when the task is to create or edit a **technical-topic slide deck** that has short intro per concept, code snippets on slides, and full runnable examples in a numbered folder (e.g. like the JavaScript web-dinámica deck).

Reference deck: [projects/generated_slides/web_dinamica_javascript.md](projects/generated_slides/web_dinamica_javascript.md).

---

## 1. Before you start: ask these questions (pragmatic)

**Ask only what the user has not already specified.** Once you have the answers you need, generate the deck and/or examples. Do not invent defaults for language or audience — if missing, ask.

1. **Topic / title** — What is the presentation about? (e.g. "OOP in Python", "Web dinámica con JavaScript")
2. **Audience / level** — Who is it for? (e.g. students SMR1, developers)
3. **Language** — In which language should the slides and speaker notes be? (e.g. Spanish, English)
4. **Duration** — Approximate length? (e.g. 35 min)
5. **How examples run** — How will attendees run the examples? (e.g. open `index.html` in browser, run `python main.py`)
6. **Outline** — Does the user provide a section/outline or should you propose one from the topic?
7. **Slide output path** — Where to write the generated Slidev markdown? (default: `projects/generated_slides/<topic>.md`)
8. **Examples path** — Where do the numbered example folders live? (default: `projects/supporting_materials/<topic>/ejemplos/`)

Optional: **Stack / theme** — Any tech stack or theme preference (e.g. Vue, React, light-only).

---

## 2. Default paths (after project restructure)

- **Generated slide file:** `projects/generated_slides/<topic>.md` (e.g. `web_dinamica_javascript.md`).
- **Supporting materials and examples:** `projects/supporting_materials/<topic>/ejemplos/` with numbered folders `01-nombre-concepto`, `02-...`.

The user can override these when answering the questions above.

---

## 3. Slidev format and style

### Title slide (first slide)

- **Background:** Dark (`#1a1a1a`), **text:** white (`#ffffff`).
- **Content:** Title (h1) and subtitle (h2) only — no "Presiona Espacio" or similar.
- **Style block** on the title slide to enforce white headings and fast transitions, and to define theme-aware callout/preview styles:

```html
<style>
:global(:root) {
  --slidev-transition-duration: 0.2s;
}
.slidev-layout h1,
.slidev-layout h2 { color: #ffffff !important; }

/* Theme-aware callout and preview boxes (avoid hardcoded #1e1e1e / #2d2d2d in content) */
.slidev-layout .slide-callout {
  background-color: #2d2d2d;
  color: #fff;
}
.slidev-layout .slide-preview-box {
  background-color: #1e1e1e;
  color: #fff;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
}
/* Light mode overrides */
html:not(.dark) .slidev-layout .slide-callout {
  background-color: #e5e7eb;
  color: #1a1a1a;
}
html:not(.dark) .slidev-layout .slide-preview-box {
  background-color: #f4f4f5;
  color: #1a1a1a;
  border-color: #e5e7eb;
}
</style>
```

Use classes `slide-callout` and `slide-preview-box` in the slide content instead of inline `bg-[#2d2d2d]` / `bg-[#1e1e1e]`.

### Transitions

- **Direction:** `slide-right` or `slide-left` (new slide enters in that direction).
- **Speed:** Fast — `--slidev-transition-duration: 0.2s` in `:root` (see style block).
- Set `transition: slide-right` (or slide-left) in frontmatter.

### Callout and preview boxes

- Use **theme-aware classes** so light/dark mode works: `slide-callout` for highlight/callout blocks, `slide-preview-box` for code-preview or small demo areas.
- Example: `<div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-lg slide-callout text-left">...</div>` and `<div class="slide-preview-box rounded-lg p-4">...</div>`.
- Do not hardcode `#1e1e1e` or `#2d2d2d` in slide content; rely on the style block above.

### Content slides

- Use `layout: default` for normal content.
- Use `layout: section` with `class: text-center` for section dividers.
- Do not set a background on content slides unless needed; let the theme apply its default.

### Frontmatter default

```yaml
---
theme: seriph
background: '#1a1a1a'   # only on title slide
class: text-center
transition: slide-right
mdc: true
title: Your Presentation Title
info: |
  ## Subtitle or short description
duration: 35min
---
```

### Layouts and typography

- Use `layout: two-cols` or a custom class like `slide-two-cols` for code + preview side-by-side (see reference deck).
- Clear font sizes (min 24px for body), sans-serif, consistent spacing (UnoCSS utilities).
- Code: syntax highlighting, monospace, concise snippets.

### Optional light palette

For full light theme: backgrounds #FFFFFF / #F4F5F7, accents #EDF6FE, #84C1FA, text #1a1a1a. The style block overrides above already adapt callouts for light mode.

